    dc:creator "Jałoszyński, Paweł; Perkovsky, Evgeny" ;
    dc:date "2016" ;
    dc:title "Diversity of Scydmaeninae (Coleoptera: Staphylinidae) in Upper Eocene Rovno amber" ;
    fabio:hasPart <http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.262415>, <http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.262450>, <http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.262451>, <http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.262449> ;
    a fabio:JournalArticle .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.262415>
    dc:description "FIGURES 21 – 34. Specimens of Rovno amber with inclusions of Scydmaeninae. K- 8972, Rovnoscydmus sp. specimen 8 (21); K- 3322, Rovnoscydmus sp. specimen 9 (22); K- 15548,? Rovnoscydmus sp. specimen 10 (23); K- 8971,? Rovnoscydmus sp. specimen 11 (24); K- 6045, Euconnus palaeogenus sp. n. (25); K- 9126, Euconnus sp. 1 (26); K- 24859,? Euconnus sp. 2 (27); K- 24302, Stenichnus proavus sp. n. (28); UA- 2216, Microscydmus sp. 1 (29); K- 6943,? Microscydmus sp. 2 (30); K- 3657 a,? Microscydmus sp. 3 (31); K- 6764,? Scydmoraphes sp. 1 (32); K- 6274, Glandulariini gen. & sp. indet. 1 (33); K- 7089, Glandulariini gen. & sp. indet. 2 (34)." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/262415/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.262450>
    dc:description "FIGURES 176 – 179. Holotype of Euconnus palaeogenus sp. n. (K- 6045). Habitus in nearly dorsal (176), ventral (178) and dorsolateral (179) views, and head in dorsal view (177). Abbreviations: abp, antebasal pit; bef, basal elytral fovea; bst, basisternal part of prosternum; cl, clypeus; fr, frons; hy, hypomeron; hypomeral ridge; lbr, labrum; mcp, mesocoxal projection; md, mandible; msvp, mesoventral intercoxal process; mtvp, metaventral intercoxal process; mxp 3 – 4, maxillary palpomere III – IV; nr, ' neck' region; nss, notosternal suture; slc, sublateral carina; tm, temple; v 3, metaventrite; vt, vertex." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/262450/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.262451>
    dc:description "FIGURES 180 – 181. Holotype of Euconnus palaeogenus sp. n. (K- 6045). Left lateral (180) and right laterodorsal (181) views. Abbreviations: dlf, dorsolateral fovea; vlf, ventrolateral fovea." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/262451/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.262449>
    dc:description "FIGURES 171 – 175. Holotype of Euconnus palaeogenus sp. n. (K- 6045). Habitus in dorsolateral (171), ventrolateral (172), nearly dorsal (173), dorsal (174) and lateral (175) views." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/262449/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

